### =========================================================================
### PHASE 1: USER REGISTRATION (Create Clean Database Records)
### =========================================================================

### 1. Register an Admin Account
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "System Administrator", 
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### 2. Register a Passenger Account
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "test 1Passenger",
  "email": "passenger@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "passenger"
}

### 3. Register a Driver Account
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "test Driver",
  "email": "driver@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "driver"
}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 2: LOGIN & GENERATE JWT TOKENS (Saves tokens into variables)
### =========================================================================

### 1. Login as Admin
# @name adminLogin
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store Admin Token
@adminToken = {{adminLogin.response.body.access_token}}

### -------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 2. Login as Passenger
# @name passengerLogin
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "passenger@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store Passenger Token
@passengerToken = {{passengerLogin.response.body.access_token}}

### -------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 3. Login as Driver
# @name driverLogin
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "driver@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store Driver Token
@driverToken = {{driverLogin.response.body.access_token}}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 3: THE CORRECT FLOW (How the system should work logically)
### =========================================================================

### 1. Passenger Requests a Trip (Passenger ID is taken automatically from Token)
POST http://localhost:3000/trips
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{passengerToken}}

{
  "startLocation": "Al-Hashimi Al-Shamali",
  "endLocation": "Petra Ride"
}

### 2. Driver Completes the Trip (Make sure Trip ID in URL matches the created trip)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "status": "completed"
}

### 3. Passenger Leaves a High Rating (5 Stars -> Auto Approved)
POST http://localhost:3000/ratings
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{passengerToken}}

{
  "tripId": 1,
  "stars": 5,
  "comment": "Excellent service!"
}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 4: SECURITY & ROLE TESTING (Testing to get 403 Forbidden Errors)
### =========================================================================

### SECURITY TEST A: Driver tries to request a trip (Should fail!)
POST http://localhost:3000/trips
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "startLocation": "Downtown",
  "endLocation": "Amman Mall"
}

### SECURITY TEST B: Passenger tries to complete a trip (Should fail!)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{passengerToken}}

{
  "status": "completed"
}

### SECURITY TEST C: Driver tries to view Pending Ratings for Admin (Should fail!)
GET http://localhost:3000/ratings/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 5: ADMIN MANAGEMENT & REPORTING (Admin Only Routes)
### =========================================================================

### Get All Registered Users
GET http://localhost:3000/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get All Active Drivers Only
GET http://localhost:3000/users/drivers
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get System Trip History
GET http://localhost:3000/trips
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get All Pending Review Ratings
GET http://localhost:3000/ratings/pending
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}